ers": {"type": "object", "properties": {"plan": {"description": "Markdown text describing the step-by-step plan (bullet list).", "title": "Plan", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["plan"]}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "check_progress", "description": "Log a progress note and return a JSON snapshot of deliverables + plan excerpt.\n\nAppends `<UTC ISO timestamp> <note>` to `workspace/.progress.log`, then\nreturns a JSON string containing:\n  - `output_files`: list of {name, size_bytes} under `workspace/output/`.\n  - `success_artifact_present`: whether the task's success artifact glob matches.\n  - `plan_excerpt`: first 1000 chars of `.plan.md` (or empty if missing).\n  - `note_count`: total notes logged so far.", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"note": {"description": "Short progress note to append to the log (plain text, one line).", "title": "Note", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["note"]}}}, {"type": "function", "info": {"name": "submit_done", "description": "End the episode. Set success=true only if criteria met (agent-declared).", "parameters": {"type": "object", "properties": {"success": {"description": "Whether the agent believes the task objective is satisfied.", "title": "Success", "type": "boolean"}, "summary": {"default": "", "description": "Short optional note for logging.", "title": "Summary", "type": "string"}}, "required": ["success"]}}}], "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "# Task `chipseq_plot_homer_annot`\n\n# Real R-task: chipseq_plot_homer_annot\n\n**Pipeline provenance:** `snakemake-workflows-chipseq-finish` (family: `chipseq`, stage: `late`, difficulty: `2`).\nThis workspace is derived from a real R script in the source workflow. The ground-truth\nreference output used for offline scoring lives outside this workspace and is not\naccessible to you during execution.\n\n## Your goal\n\nYou are given three HOMER annotatePeaks outputs under `input/`: `sampleA_annot.txt`,\n`sampleB_annot.txt`, `sampleC_annot.txt` (tab-separated, HOMER schema). For each\nsample, aggregate feature counts by the first whitespace token of `Annotation`,\nthen cast to a wide matrix (`sample` x feature). Save to\n`output/homer_annot_summary.tsv` via `write.table(..., sep='\\t', row.names=F,\ncol.names=T, quote=F)`. Do not emit any PDF plot.\n\n## Deliverables\n\n- At least `output/homer_annot_summary.tsv` must exist when you submit.\n- Full output set expected: homer_annot_summary.tsv under `output/`.\n\nWhen the deliverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"sampleA_annot.txt\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA_annot.txt\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB_annot.txt\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB_annot.txt\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC_annot.txt\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC_annot.txt\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/homer_annot_summary.tsv` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_6eVTysL82djpEV2k4B2CqyVG", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"## Plan\\n\\n1. **Load Required Libraries**: Ensure `dplyr` and `tidyr` are available for data manipulation and reshaping.\\n\\n2. **Define File Paths**: Specify the input file paths and the output file path.\\n\\n3. **Process Each File**:\\n   - Read each input file into a data frame.\\n   - Extract the `Annotation` column and split it by whitespace to get the feature name.\\n   - Count occurrences of each feature.\\n   - Reshape the data into a wide format with features as columns.\\n\\n4. **Combine Results**: Bind the results from each file into a single data frame.\\n\\n5. **Write Output**: Save the combined data frame to `output/homer_annot_summary.tsv` as a tab-separated file without row names, with column names, and without quotes.\\n\\n6. **Verify Output**: Check that the output file is correctly generated and contains the expected data.\\n\\n7. **Submit Completion**: Once the output file is verified, submit the task as complete.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (915 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_6eVTysL82djpEV2k4B2CqyVG"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_H754BCEdNwcWY0zzxlcdccaA", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"# Load necessary libraries\\nif (!requireNamespace('dplyr', quietly = TRUE)) install.packages('dplyr')\\nif (!requireNamespace('tidyr', quietly = TRUE)) install.packages('tidyr')\"}", "name": "run_rscript"}}, {"id": "call_91G67EHAXKoxeBcqbaAomEX8", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{}", "name": "list_workdir"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "exit=0\nstdout:\n\nstderr:\n", "name": "run_rscript", "tool_call_id": "call_H754BCEdNwcWY0zzxlcdccaA"}, {"role": "tool", "content": "{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"sampleA_annot.txt\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA_annot.txt\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB_annot.txt\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB_annot.txt\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC_annot.txt\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC_annot.txt\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}", "name": "list_workdir", "tool_call_id": "call_91G67EHAXKoxeBcqbaAomEX8"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_VFCWrQ7OtP7XfWml4oWOx6Uk", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"# Define input and output file paths\\ninput_files <- c('input/sampleA_annot.txt', 'input/sampleB_annot.txt', 'input/sampleC_annot.txt')\\noutput_file <- 'output/homer_annot_summary.tsv'\\n\\n# Function to process each file\\nprocess_file <- function(file) {\\n  data <- read.table(file, header = TRUE, sep = \\\"\\\\t\\\")\\n  data <- data %>%\\n    mutate(Feature = sapply(strsplit(as.character(Annotation), \\\" \\\"), `[`, 1)) %>%\\n    count(Feature) %>%\\n    spread(Feature, n, fill = 0)\\n  return(data)\\n}\\n\\n# Process each file and combine results\\nresults <- lapply(input_files, process_file)\\ncombined_results <- do.call(rbind, results)\\n\\n# Write the combined results to a TSV file\\nwrite.table(combined_results, file = output_file, sep = \\\"\\\\t\\\", row.names = FALSE, col.names = TRUE, quote = FALSE)\"}", "name": "run_rscript"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "exit=1\nstdout:\n\nstderr:\nError in scan(file = file, what = what, sep = sep, quote = quote, dec = dec,  : \n  line 2 did not have 19 elements\nCalls: lapply -> FUN -> read.table -> scan\nExecution halted\n", "name": "run_rscript", "tool_call_id": "call_VFCWrQ7OtP7XfWml4oWOx6Uk"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_CAPmc2Okb5Ru0UHo8JUAY5ao", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"relative_path\": \"input/sampleA_annot.txt\"}", "name": "read_text_file"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "PeakID\tChr\tStart\tEnd\tStrand\tPeak Score\tFocus Ratio/Region Size\tAnnotation\tDetailed Annotation\tDistance to TSS\tNearest PromoterID\tEntrez ID\tNearest Unigene\tNearest Refseq\tNearest Ensembl\tGene Name\tGene Alias\tGene Description\tGene Type\nsampleA_0\tchr1\t1000\t1500\t+\t356\t0.5\tpromoter-TSS (NM_000759)\tpromoter-TSS (NM_000759)\t-20744\tNM_0001679\tNA\tNA\tNA\tNA\tGENE_X\t\t\tprotein-coding\nsampleA_1\tchr1\t1050\t1550\t+\t26\t0.5\t3' UTR (NM_000913)\t3' UTR (NM_000913)\t\t\tNA\tNA\tNA\tNA\tGENE_X\t\t\tprotein-coding\nsampleA_2\tchr1\t1100\t1600\t+\t111\t0.5\tpromoter-TSS (NM_000095)\tpromoter-TSS (NM_000095)\t16237\tNM_0009195\tNA\tNA\tNA\tNA\tGENE_X\t\t\tprotein-coding\nsampleA_3\tchr1\t1150\t1650\t+\t311\t0.5\t3' UTR (NM_000665)\t3' UTR (NM_00066